# Parallel-drain merge friction control (CLAUDE.md §7).
#
# These release-plumbing / generated files are the ones multiple
# in-flight branches would otherwise collide on. `union` keeps both
# sides' added lines for append-style files so independent branches
# merge without a hard conflict; `.mo` is a CI-recompiled binary and
# must never be text-merged.
#
# Pair this with: git config rerere.enabled true  (replays known
# conflict resolutions, e.g. the version line).

CHANGES.md        merge=union
readme.txt        merge=union
SEQUENCE.md       merge=union
languages/*.po    merge=union
languages/*.mo    binary

# Note: never put CODE files under merge=union — it would keep both
# versions of a conflicting line and silently break the code. union is
# only safe for append-only text. The version constant lives in
# talenttrack.php (NOT unioned) and is owned solely by the release step.
